<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-lg-3">
    <nav class="sticky-lg-top pt-3">
      <div class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <a href="#conduct" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Player Conduct</a>
        <a href="#equipment" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Equipment</a>
        <a href="#scheduling" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Scheduling</a>
        <a href="#challenges" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Challenges & Matches</a>
        <a href="#disputes" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Disputes</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </div>

  <div class="col-lg-9">
    <h1 class="mb-4"><i class="bi bi-book"></i> TopMinton Rules & Guidelines</h1>
    <p class="lead text-secondary">Welcome to our community! These rules ensure a fun, respectful, and fair experience for everyone.</p>

    <section id="conduct" class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="bi bi-handshake"></i> Player Conduct</h2>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Respect & Sportsmanship</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Treat all players with respect, regardless of skill level. Avoid negative comments, excessive celebrating, or taunting. Badminton is a social sport—enjoy the game and the company of your opponent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Punctuality</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Arrive on time for scheduled matches. Notify your opponent at least 1 hour in advance if you need to reschedule. Repeatedly canceling matches may result in account suspension.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Honesty</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Play honestly and call fouls fairly. If you're unsure about a line call, the benefit of the doubt goes to the opponent. Do not falsify match results or ratings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="equipment" class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="bi bi-gear"></i> Equipment</h2>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Shuttle Types</h5>
          <p class="card-text">TopMinton players use either feather shuttles (natural cork and feathers) or plastic shuttles (synthetic). When hosting a match, specify which type you prefer. Respect others' preferences—they may have allergies, equipment, or court availability concerns.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Racquets & Apparel</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Bring a properly strung badminton racquet in good condition. Wear appropriate athletic clothing and non-marking court shoes. Do not wear street clothes or outdoor shoes on court.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Court Setup</h5>
          <p class="card-text">If you're hosting a match, ensure the court meets basic standards: proper dimensions, good lighting, and a clean playing surface. Bring your own shuttles if possible; communicate expectations in advance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="scheduling" class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="bi bi-calendar-event"></i> Scheduling & Hosting</h2>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Creating Hosted Matches</h5>
          <p class="card-text">When you host a match, provide a clear title, date/time, location, and max number of players. Be honest about court quality and facilities. Update your listing if circumstances change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Joining Matches</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Confirm your attendance when you join a hosted match. If you can no longer play, notify the host as soon as possible. No-shows without notice may affect your community reputation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Match Duration</h5>
          <p class="card-text">A typical friendly match lasts 30–60 minutes. Agree on best-of-three or best-of-five before play begins. Agree on tie-break rules (e.g., first to 15 at 20-20) to avoid disputes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="challenges" class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="bi bi-send"></i> Direct Challenges</h2>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Sending a Challenge</h5>
          <p class="card-text">When challenging another player, propose a specific date, time, and location. Include a friendly message. Respect their response—not all players will accept.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Accepting or Declining</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Respond to challenges within 48 hours. If you decline, a brief explanation is courteous. Repeated ignored challenges may reflect poorly on your profile.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Recording Results</h5>
          <p class="card-text">After a match, one player records the result (winner and optional score). Report the true outcome. Match history contributes to your public profile and reputation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="disputes" class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-circle"></i> Disputes & Enforcement</h2>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Resolving Disagreements</h5>
          <p class="card-text">If a dispute arises during a match, pause play and discuss calmly. In a friendly setting, err on the side of grace. If you cannot agree, you may replay that point or end the match amicably.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Reporting Violations</h5>
          <p class="card-text">If another player violates these rules (e.g., hostile behavior, false results, repeated no-shows), report it via your profile or contact the admin. We take community standards seriously.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card tile mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Account Suspension</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Serious violations (harassment, fraud, repeated cancellations) may result in warnings or account suspension. Our goal is a safe, inclusive community.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="card tile bg-body-tertiary mt-5">
      <div class="card-body text-center">
        <h5 class="card-title">Questions?</h5>
        <p class="card-text">If you have questions about these rules or your match experience, feel free to contact us.</p>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary"><i class="bi bi-house"></i> Back home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
